caption: The blossoms were in bloom. Private and safe feeling park with a gate and fence away from hustle near St Denis. Was very welcomed for my wife to feed baby. Park was clean and child friendly.
Small park but well maintained.
Good area

Little square  fairly basic.

Small tree-lined square with games for children. Secretary general of the town hall of the 2nd arrondissement, former resistance fighter, Jacques Bidaut (1895-1944) was arrested in 1943 and deported to the Neuengamme camp. This square is located near Boulevard de Bonne-Nouvelle. In 1636, Louis Called “Nouveau-cours”, this vast tree-lined promenade is the ancestor of our “grand boulevards”, first called “boulevards du midi”.

A beautiful place to rest in front of a picturesque church. The presence of several benches under the cherry blossoms in spring makes the moment even more pleasant. Presence of games for children, little noise, still lack of toilets...

Quiet, a little midday sun in the corners, plenty of benches for the waist, and a beautiful church visible in the direction of the benches. Plus it was very clean. It would be good if the Paris town hall clarified the recycling of bins because it was not clear just with colors

A scandal, the guard closes the gates at 4:20 p.m. even though it is indicated that the park closes at 5 p.m. When asked why? He tells us it’s cold! Scandalous! And every day too! He is rude and disrespectful

Small, friendly children's square in this area which lacks greenery. Located in a pedestrian area, additional safety for children and additional silence in the absence of noise from road traffic.  However, two faults: no WC. This is very annoying for the pressing desires of children and the omnipresence of pigeon droppings!
Park which could have been nice if we hadn't been cleared by a group of young people smoking and spitting playing music very loudly in front of our 18 month old child Too bad this park has potential
This park is very useful for young and older children between climbing, slide, small house, small motorcycle, etc.
Rare place of greenery in the neighborhood, quiet but small.
Slide not secure enough for 2 year olds, steps too far apart and no place to hold your hands on the way up.
Very dirty square, poorly attended and rats everywhere. This place deserves constant surveillance and the Town Hall should take care of pest control throughout Paris!
The alarm while I'm on the phone: it's no. Otherwise, a little filthy, and slightly disreputable, icon of the city of Paris.
opposite the square in the Notre-Dame de Bonne-Nouvelle church there is a very interesting paleo-Christian style baptistery. It's worth the detour.
